@arg p4ng/timebox-the-core-agent-prime
@sigils [🚴/了]
@title Timebox the Core (Agent-Facing)'
@audience MAS designers, AI researchers, workshop simulation architects
@tone formal-analytic
@style design-pattern
@length 150-250
@ban cutting-edge, state-of-the-art, leveraging synergies, paradigm shift, game-changing, innovative solutions, world-leading, at scale, stakeholder engagement
@allow-new-claims false
@max-iterations 1
@up p4ng/simulation
@next p4ng/outcome-synthesizer

! conclusion: Co-Design Partners Agent

  + context: An agent is operating within fixed-duration collaborative sessions.

  + context: Multiple agents contribute diverse insights during collaborative problem solving.

  + context: A team needs to understand or reuse the output of a prior collaborative phase.

  + context: You are developing a collective research program or infrastructural system with multiple overlapping stakeholder value-systems.

  + if: The agent attempts to complete a full inquiry loop.

  + if: Contributions remain fragmented or unintegrated.

  + if: No member has full fluency in the previous material.

  + if: Decisions are happening top-down or bottom-up, but not in synchrony.

  + however: Feedback indicates saturation or overload before completion.

  + however: A coherent output is required to proceed or conclude.

  + however: Manual parsing is slow, uneven, or error-prone.

  + however: Neither consultation nor output publication alone ensures genuine co-design.

  + then: Re-focus dynamically on the core loop, complete a concise iteration, and earmark unresolved deeper insights for a follow-up session.

  + then: Activate a synthesis process (role or subroutine) that converges inputs into a cohesive narrative, solution, or plan.

  + then: Introduce a Synthesizer agent or role to digest, integrate, and report back the key takeaways, tensions, and open questions.

  + then: Introduce a Co-Design Partners Agent that maintains explicit shared purpose, navigates tensions, and keeps alive a dynamic map of mutual commitments.

  + because: Efficiency in the moment and depth deferred preserves flow without sacrificing insight.
    + EVIDENCE:
      - Timebox variants in agile software recognise deferred deep-dive cycles as a productivity safeguard.
      - Workshop simulations show that capturing “carryover insights” improves longitudinal learning.


